cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the clustering and prediction of patent citation networks, which involves techniques such as Stochastic Block Model and Long Short Term Memory. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Cybernetics (cs.CY). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category as it specifically deals with network analysis and community detection. cs.IR and cs.DL are also relevant as they involve information retrieval and analysis of large datasets. cs.LG and cs.CY are less likely but still possible as they deal with machine learning and control systems, respectively, which are relevant to the techniques used in this paper.
